    <item>
      <title>Databricks Connect: Run Spark Code from Your Local IDE</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/2026/05/08/databricks-connect/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 08 May 2026 00:00:00 -0500</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/2026/05/08/databricks-connect/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;why-databricks-connect&#34;&gt;Why Databricks Connect?&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The Databricks web notebook is great for interactive exploration, but sometimes you want to:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Use your preferred local IDE (VS Code, PyCharm, etc.)&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Version control your code with git&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Run scripts in CI/CD pipelines&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Debug with local tools&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Databricks Connect lets you do all of this while still using a remote Databricks cluster for compute.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
