    <item>
      <title>Mass General Brigham EHR Data: A Real-World Data Resource for Research</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/2026/05/08/mgb-ehr-data/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 08 May 2026 00:00:00 -0500</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/2026/05/08/mgb-ehr-data/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;what-is-mass-general-brigham&#34;&gt;What Is Mass General Brigham?&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Mass General Brigham (MGB), formerly Partners HealthCare, is one of the largest academic health systems in the United States. It includes Massachusetts General Hospital, Brigham and Women&amp;rsquo;s Hospital, and several other hospitals and community health centers across New England. The system serves millions of patients and generates rich longitudinal electronic health record (EHR) data.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
